<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,375,1378,1403]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
<typeStatus box="[192,260,1379,1403]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Type</typeStatus>
species.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille, 1883" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1883" box="[382,788,1378,1403]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pythonides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="assecla">
<emphasis box="[382,610,1378,1402]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Pythonides assecla</emphasis>
Mabille, 1883
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[192,1441,1427,1847]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,338,1427,1451]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Definition.</emphasis>
A genus clearly near 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman and Salvin, 1895" authorityName="Godman and Salvin" authorityYear="1895" box="[624,1082,1427,1452]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Gindanes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[624,741,1427,1451]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Gindanes</emphasis>
Godman and Salvin, 1895
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hubner, [1819]" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[1098,1434,1427,1452]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pythonides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1098,1232,1427,1451]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Pythonides</emphasis>
HÃ¼bner, [1819]
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Lindsey, 1925" authorityName="Lindsey" authorityYear="1925" box="[192,480,1460,1484]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Quadrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[192,300,1460,1484]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Quadrus</emphasis>
Lindsey, 1925
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Evans, 1953" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1953" box="[491,704,1460,1484]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Zera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[491,547,1461,1484]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Zera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[555,704,1460,1484]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" pagination="26 - 53" refId="ref27534" refString="Evans, W. H. 1953. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part III. Pyrginae. Section 2. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 246 p., pl. 26 - 53" type="book chapter" year="1953">Evans, 1953</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Lindsey, 1925" authorityName="Lindsey" authorityYear="1925" box="[764,1030,1460,1484]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ouleus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[764,849,1460,1484]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Ouleus</emphasis>
Lindsey, 1925
</taxonomicName>
, but without closer affinity to any one of them (
<figureCitation box="[355,427,1493,1517]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="14.[192,275,1196,1218]" captionTargetBox="[193,1440,213,1161]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[192,1440,213,1162]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figure 5. Genomic trees of Achlyodini. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677245" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677245/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). The species included here in this genus were formerly placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[1248,1382,1493,1517]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pythonides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1248,1382,1493,1517]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Pythonides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but are not monophyletic with the 
<typeStatus box="[574,627,1527,1551]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">type</typeStatus>
species of this genus, 
<taxonomicName authority="Stoll, 1782" authorityName="Stoll" authorityYear="1782" box="[904,1249,1526,1550]" class="Insecta" family="Papilionidae" genus="Papilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jovianus">
<emphasis box="[904,1105,1526,1550]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Papilio jovianus</emphasis>
Stoll, 1782
</taxonomicName>
. Keys to E. 
<quantity metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0541" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" unit="in" value="41.5">41.5 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[225,391,1559,1583]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" pagination="26 - 53" refId="ref27534" refString="Evans, W. H. 1953. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part III. Pyrginae. Section 2. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 246 p., pl. 26 - 53" type="book chapter" year="1953">Evans (1953)</bibRefCitation>
. Morphologically, distinguished from related genera by the combination of the shape of uncus (flattened at the tip with a short and thin central projection) with the shape of valva (broad at the base with concave costa and diamond-shaped harpe longer than the rest of the valva, with serrated dorsoposterior edge), only one upper spur on hind tibiae, the lack of tuft in hind tibiae and thoracic pouch in males, ventral hindwing mostly pale blue, dorsal hindwing pale blue in males at least near tornus. In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly 
<date box="[995,1103,1724,1748]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" value="1672-03-01">1672.3.1</date>
:T128G, aly 
<date box="[1238,1345,1724,1748]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" value="1672-03-01">1672.3.1</date>
:C110G, aly 
<date box="[229,339,1757,1781]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" value="2618-05-01">2618.5.1</date>
:C3626G, aly140.1.2:T1822T (not A), aly 
<date box="[854,963,1757,1781]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" value="1349-07-09">1349.7.9</date>
:C1010C (not G), aly1877.13.1:A785A (not C), aly23605.1.46:T5641T (not A), aly23605.1.46:C5642C (not G), aly536.102.1:C56C (not A), aly 
<date box="[228,333,1822,1846]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" value="1935-02-01">1935.2.1</date>
:G242G (not C), aly345.3.1:C328C (not G), aly767.12.13:C118C (not A).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="13" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[192,1440,1871,1929]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,347,1871,1895]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is a feminine noun in the nominative singular, from the Latin lividus (blue), to indicate the distinctive cornflower blue color of the hindwing in males of the 
<typeStatus box="[1129,1182,1905,1929]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">type</typeStatus>
species.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677245" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3677245" box="[192,972,1196,1218]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677245/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" startId="14.[192,275,1196,1218]" targetBox="[193,1440,213,1161]" targetPageId="14">
<paragraph blockId="14.[192,972,1196,1218]" box="[192,972,1196,1218]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,303,1196,1218]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Figure 5.</emphasis>
Genomic trees of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1878" box="[500,621,1196,1218]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Achlyodini">Achlyodini</taxonomicName>
. See Fig. 2 legend for notations.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="14.[192,1118,1291,1316]" box="[192,1118,1291,1316]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,432,1291,1315]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Species included.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[493,546,1292,1316]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">type</typeStatus>
species and 
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille, 1878" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1878" box="[701,1115,1291,1316]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pythonides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandis">
<emphasis box="[701,937,1291,1315]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Pythonides grandis</emphasis>
Mabille, 1878
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[192,834,1340,1364]" box="[192,834,1340,1364]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,380,1340,1364]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Parent taxon.</emphasis>
Subtribe 
<taxonomicName authority="Grishin, 2019" authorityName="Grishin" authorityYear="2019" box="[501,830,1340,1364]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Pythonidina">Pythonidina Grishin, 2019</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[192,1440,1387,1476]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,345,1387,1411]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Comments.</emphasis>
Another genus that would be very difficult to detect without genomic data, because by appearance the adults of this species do not look noticeably different from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[1073,1207,1419,1443]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pythonides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1073,1207,1419,1443]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Pythonides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, genomic analysis suggests that the two are distant.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
